  Although this ball is made in China, Wilson headquarters are a few miles from home, here in Chicago, IL.I play these balls in my gym, and they are great, I loved them from the first time I used them. I bought one for myself, and as other reviewers have noted, they are outstanding balls to be played on an indoors court. Do not play this on the street, or else they will last a couple of months. Otherwise, this is easily the first choice when it comes to a ball for any use other than professional NBA basketball (I believe they use Spaulding).I waited until the price went down, and I paid $41.41.The company claims the ball comes ready to play out of the box, but this was not my case. The pressure on my ball was 3 psi, when it needed to be 8, so I am happy I had my super kit ready to fix that (


Franklin Sports Ball Maintenance Kit: Pump, Needles & Pressure Gauge












  ) which I highly recommend you buy. This is nothing you should be worried about, as I am assuming mostly anybody has a gauge. Thus, I am not taking a star off for it, this is a solid 5 stars product that I highly recommend without hesitation. Great deal, and great ball!
